HEADWORD: Frontignan
<hw>Fron`ti`gnan"</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from
<ets>Frontignan</ets>, a town in Southern France.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A sweet muscadine wine made in Frontignan (Languedoc),
France.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A grape of many varieties and
colors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frontingly</ent>⟦br⟧
